   @{b}Personal Paint@{ub}    - Cloanto
   @{b}Vidi Amiga 12@{ub}     - Rombo
   @{b}Pro Tracker Pro@{ub}   - Cryptoburners/RD10/OSIRIS


@{u}M a i l w a r e@{uu}
   Everytime  I see a nice game, I send the author an e-mail about it and
give  him/her my opinion. But in order to pay for the game, it has really
got  to be good. This game isn't good enough to be payed for, and that is
why I decided to make it mailware. If you like it, and would care for the
full  version, just send me an e- or snailmail. If you send snail, you've
got to include a disk and money for stamps.
   If  you  wish to include this game on a magazine's coverdisk, you have
got to do the very same thing.

These are the limitations:
   No intro
   No outro (played when last level is completed at any levelset)
   You can't save hiscore
   The game doesn't accept more than 10 levels (99 in full)
   Only one piece of ingame-music (4 or more in full)

Due  to  horrible  schoolwork etc, the full game won't be available until
beginning  of  May '98. But sendning me mail NOW, will bring you the game
as soon as it's available.


